long_description: come by and see us to try one today. established in 1996, java shack is a one-woman operation, offering a convenient drive-thru window for those on the go as well as a walk-up window along with two outdoor seating options for those who'd like to enjoy the beautiful san diego weather. featuring freshly brewed coffee and specialty espresso drinks crafted from beans obtained from locally owned la costa coffee roasting, java shack also has your sweet tooth covered with fresh baked goods from o'brien's boulangerie. craving something more substantial. java shack also offers acai bowls and handmade paninis. check out the menu to find something you'll love. move left→move right↑move up↓move down+zoom in-zoom outhomejump left by 75%endjump right by 75%page upjump up by 75%page downjump down by 75%to navigate, press the arrow keys.

generated_description: java shack is a snack and nonalcoholic beverage bar located in san diego, california. established in 1996, it operates as a one-woman business offering a variety of services including freshly brewed coffee, specialty espresso drinks, fresh baked goods from o'brien's boulangerie, acai bowls, and handmade paninis. the bar features a drive-thru window, a walk-up window, and two outdoor seating options. java shack is open monday to thursday from 7:00am to 2:00pm, and on fridays from 7:00am to 11:30am. it is closed on weekends.
